            <h1>Documentation</h1>
            <hr>
            <p><a name="intro"></a></p>
            <h3>Introduction</h3>
            <p>Welcome to The Matrix Api! This documentation should help you familiarise yourself with the resources available and how to consume them with HTTP requests. If you're after a native helper library then I suggest you scroll down and check out what's available. Read through the getting started section before you dive in. Most of your problems should be solved just by reading through it.</p>
            <p><a name="start"></a></p>
            <h3>Getting started</h3>
            <p>Let's make our first API request to The Matrix API!</p>
            <p>Open up a terminal and use <a href="http://curl.haxx.se">curl</a> or <a href="http://httpie.org">httpie</a> to make an API request for a resource. In the example below, we're trying to get the first movie, The Matrix:</p>

            <pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http thematrixapi.com/api/movies/1</code></pre>

            <p>We'll use <a href="http://httpie.org">httpie</a> for our examples as it displays responses nicely and gives us a whole lot more useful information. If you don't want to download httpie, just use the <em>curl</em> command instead.</p>

            <p>Here is the response we get:</p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "id": 4,
  "name": "The Matrix",
  "imageUrl": "https://thematrixapi.com/images/The_Matrix_1_Poster.jpg",
  "movieNumber": 1,
  "movieLength": 136,
  "director": "The Wachowskis",
  "producer": "Joel Silver",
  "distributedBy": "Warner Bros. Pictures",
  "releaseDate": "1999-03-31T00:00:00",
  "country": "United States",
  "language": "English",
  "budget": 63.00,
  "boxOffice": 464.70,
  "actors": [],
  "races": null
}
</code></pre>

            <p>If your response looks slightly different don't panic. This is probably because more data has been added to the api since we made this documentation.</p>
            <p><a name="base"></a></p>
            <h3>Base URL</h3>
            <p>The <strong>Base URL</strong> is the root URL for all of the API, if you ever make a request to "The Matrix API" and you get back a <strong>404 NOT FOUND</strong> response then check the Base URL first.</p>
            <p>The Base URL for The Matrix Api is:</p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>https://thematrixapi.com/api/</code></pre>

            <p>The documentation below assumes you are prepending the Base URL to the endpoints in order to make requests.</p>

            <p><a name="rate"></a></p>
            <h3>Rate limiting</h3>
            <p>The Matrix API has rate limiting to prevent malicious abuse (as if anyone would abuse The Matrix data!) and to make sure our service can handle a potentially large amount of traffic. Rate limiting is done via IP address and is currently limited to 10 API request per day. This is enough to request all the data on the website at least ten times over. There should be no reason for hitting the rate limit.</p>

            <p><a name="auth"></a></p>
            <h3>Authentication</h3>
            <p>The Matrix API is a <strong>completely open API</strong>. No authentication is required to query and get data. This also means that we've limited what you can do to just <strong>GET</strong>-ing the data. If you find a mistake in the data, then <a href="mailto:kalina.barzashka@gmail.com">email the author</a> about it.</p>

