            <h1>Resources</h1>
            <hr>
            <p><a name="root"></a></p>
            <h3>Root</h3>

            <p>The Root resource provides information on all available resources within the API.</p>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
    "movies": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/movies/",
    "actors": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/actors/",
    "characters": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/characters/",
    "races": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/races/",
    "quotes": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/quotes/"
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>movies</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The URL root for Movie resources
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>actors</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The URL root for Actor resources
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>characters</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The URL root for Character resources
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>races</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The URL root for Race resources
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>quotes</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The URL root for Quote resources
                </li>
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <p><a name="movies"></a></p>
            <h3>Movies</h3>
            <p>A Movie resource is a single film.</p>

            <p><strong>Endpoints</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>/movies/</code> -- get all the movies resources</li>
                <li><code>/movies/:id/</code> -- get a specific movie resource</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/movies/1/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "id": 4,
  "name": "The Matrix",
  "imageUrl": "https://thematrixapi.com/images/The_Matrix_1_Poster.jpg",
  "movieNumber": 1,
  "movieLength": 136,
  "director": "The Wachowskis",
  "producer": "Joel Silver",
  "distributedBy": "Warner Bros. Pictures",
  "releaseDate": "1999-03-31T00:00:00",
  "country": "United States",
  "language": "English",
  "budget": 63.00,
  "boxOffice": 464.70,
  "actors": [],
  "races": null
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>id</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of this movie
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>name</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name of this movie
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>imageUrl</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The image url of this movie
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>movieNumber</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The episode number of this movie.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>movieLength</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The episode duration in minutes.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>director</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name of the director of this movie.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>producer</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name(s) of the producer(s) of this movie. Comma separated.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>distributedBy</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name of the publisher company of this movie
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>releaseDate</code> <em>date</em>
                    -- The ISO 8601 date format of film release at original creator country.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>country</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The country where the movie debuts.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>language</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The official language in this movie.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>budget</code> <em>decimal</em>
                    -- How much was the initial budget of the movie.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>boxOffice</code> <em>decimal</em>
                    -- How much the movie earned money worldwide.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>actors</code> <em>array</em>
                    -- An array of actors resource URLs that are in this film.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <p><a name="actors"></a></p>
            <h3>Actors</h3>
            <p>The Actors resource is an individual person who acted as a character within the Star Wars universe.</p>

            <p><strong>Endpoints</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li><code>/actors/</code> -- get all the actors resources</li>
                <li><code>/actors/:id/</code> -- get a specific actor resource</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/actors/1/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "id": 1,
  "firstName": "Hugo",
  "middleName": "Wallace",
  "lastName": "Weaving",
  "fullName": "Hugo Wallace Weaving",
  "characterId": null,
  "character": {
    "id": 4,
    "name": "Agent Smith"
  },
  "movies": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "The Matrix 4",
      "url": "https://thematrixapi.com/api/movies/1"
    }
  ]
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>id</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of this actor.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>firstName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The first name of this actor.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>middleName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The middle name of this actor.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>lastName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The family name of this actor.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>fullName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The full name of this actor.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>character</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The character this actor is playing in the movies.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>movies</code> <em>array</em>
                    -- An array of film resource URLs that this person has been in.
                </li>      
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <p><a name="characters"></a></p>
            <h3>Characters</h3>
            <p>The Character resource is an individual person or character within the Matrix universe.</p>

            <p><strong>Endpoints</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>/characters/</code> -- get all the characters resources</li>
                <li><code>/characters/:id/</code> -- get a specific character resource</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/characters/1/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Morpheus",
  "alignment": "Good",
  "raceName": "Humans",
  "actorName": "LaurenceFishburne III",
  "quotes": []
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>id</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of this character.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>name</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name of this character.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>alignment</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The alignment of this character. Good or Bad.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>raceName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The race this character belongs to
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>actorName</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The actor playing this character
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>quotes</code> <em>array</em>
                    -- An array of notable quotes, the character says in the movies.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <p><a name="races"></a></p>
            <h3>Races</h3>
            <p>The Races resource represents the three main forces in the movies so far.</p>

            <p><strong>Endpoints</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><code>/races/</code> -- get all the races resources</li>
                <li><code>/races/:id/</code> -- get a specific race resource</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/races/1/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json
{
  "id": 1,
  "name": "Humans"
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>id</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of that race.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>name</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The name of this race.
                </li>  
            </ul>

            <hr>

            <p><a name="quotes"></a></p>
            <h3>Quotes</h3>
            <p>A Quote resource represents a notable speech, a character said in the movies.</p>

            <p><strong>Endpoints</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li><code>/quotes/</code> -- get all the quotes resources</li>
                <li><code>/quotes/:id/</code> -- get a specific quote resource</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Example request:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>http https://thematrixapi.com/api/quotes/1/
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Example response:</strong></p>

<pre class="Documentation__pre"><code>HTTP/1.0 200 OK
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "id": "1",
    "quoteLine": "How About I Give You The Finger, And You Give Me My Phone Call.",
    "characterId": "2",
    "character": {
        "id": 1,
        "name": "Neo",
        "actorName": Keanu Reeves
    }
}
</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Attributes:</strong></p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    <code>id</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of this quote.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>quoteLine</code> <em>string</em>
                    -- The notable speech itself.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>characterId</code> <em>integer</em>
                    -- The id of the character, who says the speech in the movies.
                </li>
                <li>
                    <code>character</code> <em>object</em>
                    -- The character object populated by id.
                </li>
            </ul>
          
        </div>
